This paper discusses the allocation of research funding and promotion decisions based on citation counts, which falls under the domain of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of non-parametric statistics, which is relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the classification of research based on percentile rank classes, which is relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
